Ethics II

Ethical considerations about using angioplasty balloons for proteomics analysis

Lasse Lorentzen

The project

Participants and stakeholders

  • Scientific collaborators
    • Doctors, nurses etc.
  • Actual study participants
    • A subset will also have control balloons inflated in a healthy artery
  • Future patients with cardiovascular disease

Scientific collaborators

  • Harms:
    • Hard to imagine
  • Benefits:
    • Career benefits, personal interests
  • Other ethical considerations:
    • None too obvious
  • Weight:
    • Not very important

Study participants

  • Harms:
    • Elevated risk of complications for a subset of patients
  • Benefits:
    • Feeling of “helping out”
  • Other ethical considerations:
    • Informed consent must be collected post-procedure for acute patients
  • Weight:
    • VERY important

Future patients with cardiovascular disease

  • Harms:
    • Not really
  • Benefits:
    • Improved treatment
    • Prevention of severe complications
  • Other ethical considerations:
    • Not really
  • Weight:
    • The justification of doing this

Good > Bad?

Not my decision!
